verses.text:
To whom ye forgive any thing, I \add forgive\add* also: for
if I forgave any thing, to whom I forgave \add it\add*, for your
sakes \add forgave I it\add* in the person of Christ;

To the one \add we are\add* the savour of death unto death;
and to the other the savour of life unto life. And who \add is\add*
sufficient for these things?

Who also hath made us able ministers of the new testament;
not of the letter, but of the spirit: for the letter killeth, but
the spirit giveth life.

We having the same spirit of faith, according as it is written,
I believed, and therefore have I spoken; we also believe, and therefore
speak;

Knowing therefore the terror of the Lord, we persuade men;
but we are made manifest unto God; and I trust also are made manifest
in your consciences.

And all things \add are\add* of God, who hath reconciled us
to himself by Jesus Christ, and hath given to us the ministry of
reconciliation;

For if I have boasted any thing to him of you, I am not ashamed;
but as we spake all things to you in truth, even so our boasting,
which \add I made\add* before Titus, is found a truth.

And God \add is\add* able to make all grace abound toward you;
that ye, always having all sufficiency in all \add things\add*, may
abound to every good work:

For the administration of this service not only supplieth
the want of the saints, but is abundant also by many thanksgivings
unto God;

Whiles by the experiment of this ministration they glorify
God for your professed subjection unto the gospel of Christ, and for
\add your\add* liberal distribution unto them, and unto all \add men\add*;

Casting down imaginations, and every high thing that exalteth
itself against the knowledge of God, and bringing into captivity
every thought to the obedience of Christ;
